title: Alan Webster (rower)
text:
Alan John Webster (born 18 August 1941) is a former New Zealand <a href="rowing%20%28sport%29">rower</a>.
Webster was born in <a href="Te%20Puke">Te Puke</a> in 1941.
At the <a href="1962%20British%20Empire%20and%20Commonwealth%20Games">1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games</a> he won the silver medal as part of the men's eight alongside crew members <a href="Leslie%20Arthur">Leslie Arthur</a>, <a href="Darien%20Boswell">Darien Boswell</a>, <a href="Colin%20Cordes">Colin Cordes</a>, <a href="Alistair%20Dryden">Alistair Dryden</a>, <a href="Alan%20Grey">Alan Grey</a>, <a href="Christian%20Larsen">Christian Larsen</a>, <a href="Louis%20Lobel">Louis Lobel</a> and <a href="Robert%20Page%20%28rower%29">Robert Page</a>.
Webster competed at two Olympic Games, first in <a href="New%20Zealand%20at%20the%201964%20Summer%20Olympics">1964</a> where he was part of the <a href="Rowing%20at%20the%201964%20Summer%20Olympics%20%E2%80%93%20Men%27s%20eight">men's eight</a> that made the quarter finals. Then in <a href="New%20Zealand%20at%20the%201968%20Summer%20Olympics">1968</a> where he was again part of the <a href="Rowing%20at%20the%201968%20Summer%20Olympics%20%E2%80%93%20Men%27s%20eight">men's eight</a> that came fourth in the final.
